custom-block.comment: This block is actually responsible for creating the clones and it also controls the number of chicken wings cloned.
This is the original chicken wing block. It appears randomly on the screen along with its clones.

block.comment: This is the winning condition in the game.
This block appends clones to the main sprite therby increasing its length.
These are the score intervals at which the shooting fireballs ability is granted (the intervals are the same as the intervals for the clones for the main sprite).

custom-block.comment: This block controls the movement of the cloned baby sprites as well as determines the amount of time it takes for the babies to follow the main sprite.
This is the original clone baby block that controls its movement as well.
This block controls the movement of the enemy sprites, namely Hillary Clinton, Kim Jong-un, Night King and Cersei Lannister.
This block controls the movement of the main sprite that the player controls with the mouse.

block.comment: Controls the fireball shooting ability of the main sprite.

block.l: The objective of this game is to eat 150 chickens without touching the enemies!
As you progress through the game, you will have baby sprites appended to your main sprite.
For every baby, you get the fireball shooting ability for 7 seconds.
The fireballs will make the enemies disappear for 10 seconds before they come back to kill you !
But first, choose a theme for this game!
There are two options: 1) America 2) Game of Thrones

block.comment: Responsible for the Game of Thrones theme.

block-definition.comment: LABEL will stamp text on the stage at the given font size. The direction of the text is the direction the sprite is facing, and color will match the pen color.

block.l: var stage = this.parentThatIsA(StageMorph); if (this == stage) { throw new Error( 'LABEL cannot be used from the stage because the stage does not have a postion.\n' + 'Use LABEL from a sprite to draw text.'); } if (typeof text !== 'string' && typeof text !== 'number') { throw new Error('LABEL can only draw text or numbers, not a ' + process.reportTypeOf(text)); } var context = stage.penTrails().getContext('2d'), rotation = radians(this.direction() - 90), trans = new Point( this.center().x - stage.left(), this.center().y - stage.top() ), isWarped = this.Warped, len, pos; if (isWarped) {endWarp(); } context.save(); context.font = size + 'px monospace'; context.textAlign = 'left'; context.textBaseline = 'alphabetic'; context.fillStyle = this.color.toString(); len = context.measureText(text).width; trans = trans.multiplyBy(1 / stage.scale); context.translate(trans.x, trans.y); context.rotate(rotation); context.fillText(text, 0, 0); context.translate(-trans.x, -trans.y); context.restore(); pos = new Point( len * Math.sin(radians(this.direction())), len * Math.cos(radians(this.direction()))); pos = pos.add(new Point(this.xPosition(), this.yPosition())); this.gotoXY(pos.x, pos.y, false); this.changed(); if (isWarped) {this.startWarp(); } stage.changed();
